😕 Don't know how to start keto diet properly? or want to lose 5-10 lbs in the first week alone with keto lifestyle ?
You can click link in our bio to get Everything You Need for keto Success. Imagine… armed with 4-week meal plan, 7 Keto guide books, and the 3 bonus guides… you’ll be able to start strong and finish strong. 💪 @ketomealrecipe 
.
You just can’t go wrong with pancakes, bacon and eggs👏⁣⁣
⁣
What are you making for breakfast?⁣⁣
⁣
I like both almond and coconut flour pancakes, which do you like best?⁣⁣
⁣
Save this post and share with friends that are starting keto 🙌⁣⁣
⁣

My fave is Maple and Chocolate!⁣⁣
⁣
I triple the recipe and store them in the freezer for easy breakfast options. Makes life so much easier!⁣⁣
⁣
For those of you that are new to my page, here is my blender pancake recipe 🤗⁣⁣
⁣
Throw everything in the blender, mix, cook and enjoy 🥳⁣⁣
⁣
Simple ingredients and kiddo approved🥰⁣⁣
⁣
Almond flour blender pancakes⁣⁣
⁣
4oz of cream cheese (microwave 15-30sec)⁣⁣
4 eggs (room temp)⁣⁣
3/4 cup of Almond flour⁣⁣
1 tsp baking powder⁣⁣
1-2 Tablespoons of sweetener ⁣⁣
1/2- 1tsp vanilla ⁣⁣
1/8 tsp Cinnamon⁣⁣
⁣
Coconut flour pancakes⁣⁣
⁣
•4oz cream cheese⁣⁣
•4eggs⁣⁣
•4 tableapoons of coconut flour⁣⁣
•1 1/2 teaspoons of baking powder⁣⁣
•1-2 tablespoons of sweetener⁣⁣
⁣
Optional but I always use⁣⁣
•1/2 tsp cinnamon⁣⁣
•1 tsp vanilla extract⁣⁣
•1/2 tsp maple extract⁣⁣
⁣
Directions:⁣⁣
-Put all ingredients in blender... blend for 45 seconds - 1 minute.⁣⁣
-Let sit for 10mins before cooking⁣⁣
-enjoy with butter and SF syrup *you can freeze and warm up in toaster or microwave⁣⁣
⁣
Who’s making pancakes?🙋‍♀️⁣⁣
_____________________⁣⁣

Buttery Garlic Steak Bites. Don't forget to join 28 day keto challenge for more keto recipes and instructions, get it in link in bio @ketomealrecipe

Pic credit to @keto_rebel 
-
This is officially my new favorite way to eat steak! The smaller pieces come out super tender and flavorful! I also cooked the steak in the air fryer so no messy stove, double win! 🙌🏻
⠀
Here’s the recipe: ⤵️
⠀
Ingredients:
- Steak, cut into 1/2” cubes (ribeye, sirloin, tri-tip or what you have)
- 1-2 Tablespoons butter, melted
- 1 teaspoon low sodium soy sauce or coconut aminos
- 1 teaspoon garlic, minced
- salt and pepper to taste
- 1/2 teaspoon onion powder
⠀
Instructions:
* In a bowl season the steak cubes soy sauce, onion powder, minced garlic, salt and pepper. Stir everything together until the steak is fully coated.
⠀
* Set aside and let sit at room temperature for 15 mins.
⠀
* Next, coat the steak with the melted butter. Giving everything a few good stirs.
⠀
* Spread the steak in an even layer in the air fryer basket. Air fry at 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes, shaking and flipping and the steak half way through (time depends on your preferred doneness and thickness of the steak.
⠀
* Check the steak to see how well done it is cooked. If you want the steak more done, add an extra 2-4 minutes of cooking time.
⠀
I paired my steak bites with a crispy Chopped Caesar Salad. 😋

💁 Did you know more recipes are available in 28 day challenge?💡 If you want to lose several lbs in the first week alone with ketolifestyle. Not only will you feel a huge sense of accomplishment, you’ll:
▪️Be lighter and thinner (it’s not uncommon to lose 20+ lbs!)
▪️Have more energy than you’ve felt in years.
▪️Be sleeping better and feeling more rested when you wake up.
▪️Notice improvements in your skin and hair.
▪️Probably best of all, you’ll have MOMENTUM to keep going with your new Keto lifestyles… you’ll be able to start strong and finish strong. 💪 @ketomealrecipe
-
2 cups grated zucchini
1 large egg
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
2 green onions, sliced thin
1/4 cup tapioca starch or corn starch
salt & pepper to taste
vegetable oil
2 cups shredded cheddar cheese
After shredding the zucchini, squeeze all excess moisture from them shreds using paper towels.
In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients (thru salt & pepper), until incorporated.
In a large skillet, drizzle with oil to almost coat the bottom and heat on medium high. Scoop about 1/4 cup of the mixture onto the pan and flatten em out as much as possible using a spatula so that they are thin. Repeat. Lower heat to medium and cook each patty 5-7 minutes per side. Remove and place on plate lined with paper towel to absorb excess oils. Wipe pan clean. Transfer one patty back to the pan and top with shredded cheese. Top that with another patty. Cook until cheese is melted. Repeat. Serve immediately. Yields 2-3 servings.
